The v3.1 profile's `gpu_memory_utilization` value is **0.55**.

It was picked because this project runs on a **DGX Spark with 128 GB UMA** (Unified Memory Architecture), where GPU memory is shared between model weights, KV cache, and the harness/CPU. The default vLLM `gpu_memory_utilization=0.95` (or the higher 0.88 used in v3) is too aggressive for this shared-memory setup and causes preemptions.

The KV bisection experiments on this hardware converge on a theoretical ceiling of `0.86`, but v3.1 backs off further to **0.55** to leave enough system-RAM headroom for the rest of the workload — specifically, to avoid Pitfall #3 (system RAM exhaustion from preemptions), which takes priority over pushing the KV ceiling as high as possible.
